EMES also while we are on it What EMES just did was wipeout unitholders You are getting at most 5 cents on the dollar for your shares Bond holders are forgiving the debt and taking 95 cents on the dollarCheck with your tax professional but you may be on the hook for CODI in this MLP Again this is a MasterLimited Partnership and you are getting a K1 This is a real example of the math based on my understanding of the situationYou buy 100 worth of EMES but that 100 is worth 2000 of forgiven debt You make a 100 on EMES so you have 200 but you could owe taxes on 2000 for the CODI which after all is said and done even though you invested 200 you now have to pay taxes on that 2000 income plus the 100 in capital gains taxes meaning you pay taxes on 2100 of income You can do the math for your specific situation
